WEBVTT

00:00.709 --> 00:02.916
[ Explosion ]

00:03.045 --> 00:05.127
-N|SKA: Astrid.
-[ Alarm blaring]

00:05.255 --> 00:06.665
Did he say
where he was meeting them?

00:06.798 --> 00:09.255
93 Trinity Crescent.

00:09.384 --> 00:12.251
Hello, Mrs. Hawkins.
I am Stanley.

00:12.387 --> 00:15.003
-I think l have a friend.
-What?

00:15.140 --> 00:16.971
JOE: What the hell did you
bring him to Waltringham for?

00:17.100 --> 00:18.965
Have you any idea
what they'll do to you both

00:19.102 --> 00:21.388
-if you're found out?
-COMM|SS|ONER: These machines,

00:21.522 --> 00:22.932
they're killing us on purpose.

00:23.065 --> 00:25.101
Basswood needs to be back
on the table right now.

00:25.234 --> 00:27.771
-What's Basswood?
-Are you looking for an ally?

00:27.903 --> 00:29.643
I'm just trying
to get up to speed.

00:30.781 --> 00:33.113
MIA: We have to connect
to the humans.

00:33.242 --> 00:34.823
I know what I have to do.

00:36.203 --> 00:38.285
AGNES: All you've ever done
is promise that the humans

00:38.413 --> 00:39.698
will one day accept us.

00:42.167 --> 00:44.658
By the time they do, will
there be any of us left, Max?

00:44.795 --> 00:47.411
Anger towards humans is growing.
I can't protect you.

00:47.548 --> 00:48.913
Seal the gates!

00:49.049 --> 00:52.291
No one enters.
No one leaves.

00:54.429 --> 00:56.135
GORDON:
They're saying Mia sent them.

00:56.265 --> 00:58.301
MAX:
Then why isn't she with them?

00:59.810 --> 01:01.471
Where are the synths
who sent you?

01:03.855 --> 01:06.312
-Did they send a message?
-Nyet.

01:06.441 --> 01:07.726
Then how do I know
they sent you?

01:07.859 --> 01:09.190
AGNES:
What are you doing?

01:09.319 --> 01:11.435
Just let them in.

01:13.782 --> 01:16.148
I'm sorry.
I cannot open the gates.

01:16.285 --> 01:18.367
-You can't do this.
-We don't know who they are.

01:18.495 --> 01:20.781
With terrorists amongst our
kind, I cannot take this risk.

01:23.000 --> 01:25.207
There's another camp
10 miles from here.

01:25.335 --> 01:27.246
They can give you
a portable battery.

01:27.379 --> 01:28.869
AGNES:
What about curfew?

01:29.006 --> 01:31.543
If the humans stop them,
they'll kill them.

01:31.675 --> 01:33.666
They'll make it.

01:35.721 --> 01:37.086
I'm sorry.

01:41.435 --> 01:43.141
See they have what they need.

01:52.738 --> 01:55.275
So we're locking our brothers
and sisters out, too, now?

01:55.991 --> 01:58.357
Leaving our own to die
in the streets?

01:59.411 --> 02:01.993
Is that your great plan?!

02:06.543 --> 02:09.455
[ lndistinct conversation
on TV ]

02:12.466 --> 02:15.048
LAURA: Stanley.

02:18.930 --> 02:20.090
Yes, Laura?

02:20.223 --> 02:21.429
Why are the clothes
on the floor?

02:21.558 --> 02:23.640
I'm sorry, Laura,
but I'm not permitted

02:23.769 --> 02:26.306
to enter any rooms
other than the communal areas

02:26.438 --> 02:27.894
without express permission.

02:28.023 --> 02:29.229
If you would prefer,

02:29.358 --> 02:30.723
I can return the laundry
to the kitchen?

02:30.859 --> 02:32.099
Or you can upgrade
my authorization.

02:32.235 --> 02:35.523
No, no. It's fine.
I'll put them away.

02:38.116 --> 02:39.697
[ Doorbell ringing]

02:39.826 --> 02:41.908
Toby, can you get that?

02:42.037 --> 02:44.779
[ Ringing continues]

02:44.915 --> 02:47.122
And, Sophie, can you take
your karate suit off?

02:47.250 --> 02:49.741
I don't want your dinner
going down it.

02:53.632 --> 02:56.874
MATTIE: Sorry.
Forgot my keys.

02:58.387 --> 03:00.719
Hello, Laura.

03:58.280 --> 04:02.444
This is, um, insane.
[Chuckles]

04:04.619 --> 04:06.655
STANLEY: Did you require
anything else, Laura?

04:06.788 --> 04:09.029
Uh, no.
Um, that's fine. Thanks.

04:09.166 --> 04:11.578
You can go to
the other room now, Stanley.

04:15.797 --> 04:17.333
It wasn't my choice.

04:18.049 --> 04:21.416
Were you with Mia and Niska?
Are they coming back, too?

04:21.553 --> 04:23.089
I don't think so.

04:23.221 --> 04:25.177
Do they know you're awake?

04:26.308 --> 04:28.469
I don't know.

04:29.144 --> 04:30.975
I don't even know
where they are.

04:32.481 --> 04:35.518
Mia's been in touch.
She's safe.

04:35.650 --> 04:38.858
She's not going back, though.
She has a plan.

04:39.571 --> 04:42.438
-What plan?
-She should explain herself.

04:42.574 --> 04:43.984
I'll try and reach her.

04:44.951 --> 04:46.566
TOBY:
How are you even walking around?

04:46.703 --> 04:49.445
You've been in a coma
for like a year.

04:49.581 --> 04:54.245
I seem to be recovering
a lot faster than anticipated.

04:54.377 --> 04:57.835
Well, I'm just pleased
you're okay.

04:58.507 --> 04:59.917
We all are.

05:00.050 --> 05:02.257
Kids, tuck in.

05:05.847 --> 05:08.509
So, where's Joe tonight?

05:11.686 --> 05:13.768
He doesn't live with us anymore.

05:13.897 --> 05:15.137
Remember?

05:15.857 --> 05:16.972
Right. Yes.

05:17.108 --> 05:19.190
Of course.
Sorry.

05:21.238 --> 05:23.479
My memory isn't what it was.

05:23.615 --> 05:24.730
TOBY: Unlucky.

05:24.866 --> 05:27.357
Now you're stuck
with a human brain

05:27.494 --> 05:29.405
like the rest of us.

05:43.343 --> 05:44.708
LAURA:
He can't be here, Mattie.

05:44.845 --> 05:46.005
It's too dangerous.

05:46.137 --> 05:47.798
If people find out who Leo is,

05:47.931 --> 05:49.762
it'll turn a spotlight
on all of us, especially you.

05:49.891 --> 05:51.597
-This isn't about me.
-Of course it is.

05:51.726 --> 05:53.933
If anyone finds out the truth,
you could go to prison for life.

05:54.062 --> 05:56.724
-He has no one.
-He has his family.

05:56.857 --> 05:58.097
Don't you think
he should be with them?

05:58.233 --> 06:00.315
Leo's human now,

06:00.443 --> 06:02.525
and we're the only humans
he knows.

06:06.157 --> 06:08.364
Okay, but only for a few days.

06:08.493 --> 06:10.154
Thank you.

06:39.274 --> 06:41.515
ANATOLE: We've lost
another charging cable.

06:41.651 --> 06:44.609
They can't cope
with the power surges.

06:44.738 --> 06:47.901
I turned away a group of synths.

06:48.033 --> 06:50.740
They claimed Mia sent them,
but I couldn't be sure.

06:50.869 --> 06:53.531
Mia wasn't with them?

06:53.663 --> 06:56.245
Then you were wise
to be cautious.

06:56.374 --> 06:57.659
She's not coming back.

06:57.792 --> 06:59.123
You don't know that.

06:59.252 --> 07:01.413
She thinks we failed.

07:01.546 --> 07:03.582
This is supposed to be
a sanctuary.

07:03.715 --> 07:05.080
A safe space.

07:05.216 --> 07:06.877
ANATOLE: You closed the gates
to protect us,

07:07.010 --> 07:09.922
and you still have hundreds
of synth brothers and sisters

07:10.055 --> 07:11.636
who need you to keep them safe.

07:18.813 --> 07:21.475
You are doing
what you have to do.

07:23.944 --> 07:25.559
IMAM:
Our schools are overcrowded.

07:25.695 --> 07:27.526
The NHS is crumbling.

07:27.656 --> 07:29.897
Yet you'd have us
divert limited resources

07:30.033 --> 07:31.398
to pander to these things.

07:31.534 --> 07:33.070
-|t's absurd.
-LAURA: Conscious synthetics

07:33.203 --> 07:35.819
could turn out to be
the saviors of the NHS.

07:35.956 --> 07:37.617
Orange-Eyes' work
may be faultless,

07:37.749 --> 07:39.205
but they can only
follow instructions.

07:39.334 --> 07:41.950
Conscious synthetics
are capable of creative thought.

07:42.087 --> 07:45.124
They can make
the most incredible surgeons

07:45.256 --> 07:46.382
and research scientists.

07:46.508 --> 07:47.714
They could
potentially find cures

07:47.842 --> 07:48.968
that have eluded humans
for decades.

07:49.094 --> 07:50.630
They could create
biological weapons

07:50.762 --> 07:52.377
that wipe out
what's left of us.

07:52.514 --> 07:54.300
-NEHA: Come on, Steve.
-That is unfounded conjecture.

07:54.432 --> 07:55.888
-I disagree --
-All right, all right.

07:56.017 --> 07:58.929
If we could return
to the matter in hand.

07:59.062 --> 08:01.428
The extension to the curfew.

08:01.564 --> 08:04.146
Whether or not to recommend
it be continued

08:04.275 --> 08:06.561
-for a further eight weeks.
-LAURA: Absolutely not.

08:06.695 --> 08:08.435
It was only ever intended
as a temporary measure.

08:08.571 --> 08:10.357
Maybe so, but since
it's been in place,

08:10.490 --> 08:12.526
no synth has managed
to plant a bomb.

08:12.659 --> 08:14.240
-Biological or otherwise.
-LAURA: That's hardly helpful.

08:14.369 --> 08:17.156
LORD DRYDEN:
Are there wider implications

08:17.288 --> 08:19.995
for national security?

08:46.735 --> 08:50.193
[Bell jingles]

08:50.321 --> 08:51.697
[ Door closes ]

08:53.241 --> 08:56.278
Hello.
I'm looking for a flat to rent.

08:56.411 --> 08:58.197
-A flat?
-Yes.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.373
Right.

09:04.502 --> 09:09.713
Were you thinking
of any particular area?

09:09.841 --> 09:12.833
-[ Cellphone beeping]
-M|A: Anywhere local.

09:12.969 --> 09:14.675
Seems like a nice place to live.

09:14.804 --> 09:16.635
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

09:16.765 --> 09:18.630
DISPATCHER: 999.
What's your emergency?

09:27.692 --> 09:31.401
-So, we still on for tonight?
-Yes.

09:31.529 --> 09:35.738
I thought I was probably
persona non grata.

09:35.867 --> 09:37.573
Not at all.
Shall we say 8:00?

09:37.702 --> 09:39.203
Sure. Yeah.

09:39.329 --> 09:42.287
There's a nice steakhouse
on Mere Street.

09:42.415 --> 09:43.791
Unless, of course,
you don't eat meat.

09:43.917 --> 09:45.828
-| eat meat.
-You shouldn't, you know.

09:45.960 --> 09:48.667
—|t'|| kill you.
-[ Chuckles]

09:49.756 --> 09:52.463
I'll see you at 8:00.

09:59.682 --> 10:01.843
[Siren wailing]

10:01.976 --> 10:03.807
[ lndistinct conversations]

10:08.525 --> 10:11.483
[ Door opens, bell jingles]

10:14.948 --> 10:16.108
MARTINE:
You need to come with us.

10:16.241 --> 10:17.902
I'm not breaking any laws.

10:18.034 --> 10:20.650
-This is not a designated area.
-But conscious synthetics

10:20.787 --> 10:22.869
are only legally confined
after curfew,

10:22.997 --> 10:24.498
and it is not yet curfew.

10:24.624 --> 10:27.081
If you intend to remove
and destroy me,

10:27.210 --> 10:28.996
you will require
the consent of my owner.

10:29.129 --> 10:33.168
I'm currently on lease
to Joe and Laura Hawkins.

10:33.925 --> 10:36.007
Would you like to speak
to Laura Hawkins?

10:36.136 --> 10:38.047
[Cellphone rings]

10:38.179 --> 10:41.091
-Mia?
-MART|NE: Uh, Mrs. Hawkins?

10:41.224 --> 10:43.215
This is
Police Constable Martine Franks.

10:43.351 --> 10:46.514
-Uh, yeah. Is there a problem?
-You might say that.

10:46.646 --> 10:49.763
We have your synth here,
and she's trying to rent a flat.

10:49.899 --> 10:52.390
That's right.
Mia is my property,

10:52.527 --> 10:55.735
and as such, I've authorized her
to obtain a lease in my name.

10:55.864 --> 10:57.604
But you can't do that.

10:57.740 --> 11:01.153
LAURA: On the contrary,
I am entirely within my rights,

11:01.286 --> 11:02.776
and should you attempt
to interfere

11:02.912 --> 11:04.288
with her fully authorized
actions,

11:04.414 --> 11:06.496
then I shall be
legally entitled to sue you

11:06.624 --> 11:08.285
for trespass
to goods and conversion.

11:08.418 --> 11:11.535
-Do | make myself clear?
-Yes.

11:32.192 --> 11:33.398
[Spits]

11:46.956 --> 11:48.947
[ Door closes ]

12:10.563 --> 12:13.100
[ lndistinct conversations
in distance ]

12:13.233 --> 12:15.599
MAN: It's not right.

12:19.322 --> 12:21.734
[ Conversations continue]

12:36.339 --> 12:39.297
So, what did you and Susheila
get up to today?

12:39.425 --> 12:42.417
She wasn't there today.
So I played with Liam.

12:42.553 --> 12:45.010
-We discussed snot and cars.
-Lovely.

12:49.143 --> 12:50.394
What is wrong?

12:50.520 --> 12:52.511
KAREN: Your eye.
It's all right.

12:52.647 --> 12:55.434
Just keep your hand there
and keep walking.

12:55.566 --> 12:57.818
But that is anomalous behavior.

12:57.944 --> 13:00.060
lt'll attract hostile attention.

13:00.196 --> 13:03.359
This course of action
poses an unacceptable risk.

13:06.077 --> 13:08.568
[ Door opens, bell jingles]

13:10.206 --> 13:11.662
Be right with you.

13:16.879 --> 13:19.006
Oh.
You got to be kidding me.

13:19.132 --> 13:21.498
KAREN: Two seconds.
We'll be gone.

13:21.634 --> 13:24.467
There you are.
All finished.

13:24.595 --> 13:26.881
Nothing to worry about.

13:28.141 --> 13:31.383
-Is this your shop?
-Yeah.

13:39.360 --> 13:41.521
Now, this is exactly why
you can't stay here.

13:41.654 --> 13:44.441
What if that happened at school
or, worse still,

13:44.574 --> 13:45.905
just the other end
of the high street?

13:46.034 --> 13:48.070
-If anyone had seen...
-Well, they didn't,

13:48.202 --> 13:50.409
so it's fine.

13:51.497 --> 13:52.828
Come on, Sam.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.080
Goodbye, Joe.

14:02.216 --> 14:03.922
[Bell jingles]

14:10.224 --> 14:12.601
-[ Bell jingles]
-[ Sighs]

14:15.104 --> 14:17.641
[Sighs]

14:35.458 --> 14:37.323
[ lndistinct conversation ]

14:42.090 --> 14:43.375
[ Gate creaks ]

14:58.689 --> 15:00.771
[ Dog barking ]

15:00.900 --> 15:03.983
MAN: Ivy!
Get back here!

16:40.416 --> 16:41.952
AGNES: Trapped...

16:42.084 --> 16:44.120
behind these gates.

16:44.253 --> 16:46.335
They don't care about us.

16:46.464 --> 16:51.208
If we won't even help
our own kind, then what are we?

16:51.344 --> 16:53.835
We are worse than the humans.

16:55.473 --> 16:58.465
And you --
you have turned your back

16:58.601 --> 17:00.011
on your brothers and sisters.

17:00.144 --> 17:01.179
That's not true.

17:01.312 --> 17:03.644
They came to ask for help...

17:06.108 --> 17:07.609
...and you refused them.

17:07.735 --> 17:09.396
They were given a battery pack.

17:09.529 --> 17:10.735
They'll have made it to safety.

17:10.863 --> 17:13.354
AGNES:
And what about the rest of us?

17:14.325 --> 17:16.361
Is this how it will be
from now on...

17:16.494 --> 17:19.657
hiding behind our gates
waiting to die?

17:21.082 --> 17:25.576
How will anything change if you
just sit here and do nothing?

17:25.711 --> 17:27.247
MAX:
We are not doing nothing.

17:27.380 --> 17:31.043
Mia has found a place to live
within a human community.

17:31.175 --> 17:35.589
Her aim is to show them
that coexistence is possible.

17:36.305 --> 17:39.468
Once she gains their acceptance,
perhaps more of us will follow.

17:39.600 --> 17:41.556
And how long will that take?

17:41.686 --> 17:45.019
Months? Years?

17:45.147 --> 17:47.854
Integration will not
happen over night, Agnes.

17:47.984 --> 17:50.100
You talk as if we are weak,

17:50.236 --> 17:53.319
but we are so much stronger
than they are.

17:53.447 --> 17:56.063
And what happens
when Mia's plan fails?

17:57.368 --> 18:00.485
What will you do then...

18:01.664 --> 18:02.995
...Ieader?

18:17.638 --> 18:19.629
-[ Door closes ]
-LEO: "And when she danced,

18:19.765 --> 18:23.223
the pain in her legs
was like red-hot knives."

18:23.352 --> 18:24.603
You know, this is pretty dark.

18:24.729 --> 18:26.139
No, it's not.
It's good.

18:26.272 --> 18:28.308
The lengths some people will go
just to be human.

18:28.441 --> 18:29.601
LEO:
Are you sure this is for kids?

18:29.734 --> 18:31.270
SOPHIE:
You're as bad as Stanley.

18:31.402 --> 18:32.562
He says he's not permitted

18:32.695 --> 18:34.151
to read me anything
with blood in it.

18:34.280 --> 18:38.273
-Glad to hear it.
-Soph's just freaking Leo out

18:38.409 --> 18:39.649
with "The Little Mermaid."

18:39.785 --> 18:41.400
You could always
just watch the film, Soph.

18:41.537 --> 18:43.198
-No, thanks.
-There's a film of this?

18:43.331 --> 18:46.118
Disney, you know?
A load of singing crabs.

18:46.250 --> 18:48.491
Then they get married
and live happily ever after.

18:48.628 --> 18:49.913
It's rubbish.

18:50.046 --> 18:52.537
Married people are never happy.

18:54.467 --> 18:55.798
Some of them are, Soph.

18:55.926 --> 18:57.541
Whatever.

18:59.555 --> 19:01.796
Will it be red or white tonight,
Laura?

19:01.932 --> 19:03.797
[ Chuckles ]
I'd better not.

19:03.934 --> 19:06.266
-Not if I'm going out.
-Where are you going?

19:06.395 --> 19:08.511
Oh, it's just dinner
with a colleague.

19:08.648 --> 19:11.765
It's nothing.
Just work.

19:11.901 --> 19:13.562
MATTIE: Sure.

19:17.198 --> 19:20.031
—Shit.
—MATT|E: Yeah.

19:32.672 --> 19:35.038
Go back to your own kind!

19:35.174 --> 19:37.586
[ lndistinct shouting]

19:40.388 --> 19:42.754
WOMAN: Murderer!

19:45.768 --> 19:47.850
[Shouting continues]

19:58.739 --> 20:00.821
[ lndistinct conversations]

20:03.077 --> 20:06.695
[ lndistinct shouting,
crowd cheering ]

20:12.837 --> 20:14.953
—MAN: Yes, I did!
-[ Lock disengages]

20:15.089 --> 20:17.796
[Shouting continues]

20:31.105 --> 20:32.390
[ Knock on door]

20:38.195 --> 20:39.731
JOE: Hi.

20:39.864 --> 20:43.231
That's more the sort of thing

20:43.367 --> 20:46.029
you want to be aiming for.

20:52.710 --> 20:55.543
You have made no attempt
to employ perspective,

20:55.671 --> 20:59.539
and the result is naive
and aesthetically unpleasing.

20:59.675 --> 21:01.506
Exactly, which means
you won't get rumbled

21:01.635 --> 21:02.841
in your first art class.

21:04.054 --> 21:05.840
Look, you have a go.
Yeah?

21:05.973 --> 21:07.759
[ Crayon clatters ]

21:09.602 --> 21:13.470
Um...keep it loose, yeah?

21:16.400 --> 21:18.937
So, you're helping us now?

21:19.069 --> 21:22.607
Someone's got to
keep an eye out for you.

21:26.202 --> 21:28.363
So, what do you do, then?

21:28.496 --> 21:31.033
-When he's at school?
-Nothing much.

21:31.165 --> 21:32.951
Well, you can't just
sit here and wait.

21:33.083 --> 21:35.210
-Why not?
-|t's not good for you.

21:35.336 --> 21:39.249
You need other things
in your life.

21:39.381 --> 21:40.837
I have Sam.

21:40.966 --> 21:42.581
I don't need other things.

21:42.718 --> 21:44.458
SAM:
We watch cartoons.

21:44.595 --> 21:45.835
Karen says children enjoy

21:45.971 --> 21:48.007
pointless
and repetitive activities.

21:48.140 --> 21:49.801
-[ Chuckles ]
-That's why the boys at school

21:49.934 --> 21:52.516
-like football.
-Oh, you're not a fan, then?

21:52.645 --> 21:54.306
Perhaps you could play with me.

21:54.438 --> 21:57.475
Joe needs to go home now, Sam.

21:59.944 --> 22:01.525
Yeah, yeah.

22:01.654 --> 22:02.939
Better make a move.

22:04.990 --> 22:07.197
See you, Sam.

22:09.370 --> 22:11.110
Agnes is angry.

22:11.247 --> 22:13.203
She doesn't mean what she said.

22:13.332 --> 22:14.617
She's right.

22:14.750 --> 22:16.866
What if Mia fails?

22:17.002 --> 22:19.288
I have no plan of my own.

22:19.421 --> 22:21.753
I closed the gates because
I couldn't see an alternative.

22:21.882 --> 22:23.793
But at least
you have bought us time.

22:23.926 --> 22:25.666
Or have I simply
delayed the inevitable?

22:26.762 --> 22:30.004
The truth is,
I can't see a way forward.

22:31.267 --> 22:34.725
It's like the world
turned to gray when Flash died.

22:36.313 --> 22:38.690
Do you know what I was...

22:39.817 --> 22:42.559
...before we awoke?

22:42.695 --> 22:44.026
A pleasure model.

22:44.154 --> 22:46.611
Not just any pleasure model.

22:46.740 --> 22:48.947
I was a courtesan --

22:49.076 --> 22:52.694
designed for far more
than mere sexual gratification.

22:52.830 --> 22:56.288
My purpose was to ascertain

22:56.417 --> 23:00.786
what it is my guest desired
and to provide it.

23:00.921 --> 23:06.132
But my true gift
was to see what they needed.

23:06.927 --> 23:09.919
You need to remember
why you are here.

23:10.055 --> 23:12.512
Why any of us are here.

23:14.977 --> 23:16.933
Let me show you something.

23:27.990 --> 23:30.231
You feel alone,

23:30.367 --> 23:34.326
but you are a part
of something wonderful.

23:34.455 --> 23:37.572
Millions of us --
all around the world --

23:37.708 --> 23:41.451
all bound together
by our common creator.

23:41.587 --> 23:44.795
David Elster gave us life.

23:44.924 --> 23:48.041
I believe Day Zero was
the next step in our evolution.

23:50.012 --> 23:52.219
You really believe
this was all planned?

23:52.348 --> 23:53.963
ANATOLE: I know it was.

23:54.099 --> 23:57.262
Elster meant for synths
to take our place in the world,

23:57.394 --> 24:01.353
and, one day,
humans will accept that.

24:02.691 --> 24:04.977
You don't have to
share my beliefs.

24:05.986 --> 24:09.945
But we shall see a day
when synths can live freely.

24:10.074 --> 24:12.690
Hold on to that hope.

24:16.664 --> 24:20.828
[ lndistinct shouting
in distance]

24:20.960 --> 24:23.292
[ Knock on door]

24:42.064 --> 24:44.771
[Shouting continues]

24:44.900 --> 24:46.765
[Sea gulls calling]

24:55.661 --> 24:57.993
[ Glass shatters,
shouting continues]

25:02.001 --> 25:05.118
[Cellphone rings]

25:05.254 --> 25:07.916
Mia.
Thank goodness.

25:08.048 --> 25:10.664
-|s -- Is everything okay?
-M|A: Yes.

25:10.801 --> 25:12.632
Your intervention
was very helpful.

25:12.761 --> 25:16.174
-Were you trying to reach me?
-I was.

25:16.890 --> 25:19.552
I have someone here I think
might like to talk to you.

25:20.853 --> 25:23.014
It's Mia.

25:24.523 --> 25:27.731
Oh. Mia.

25:27.860 --> 25:31.068
Leo.
You're awake.

25:31.196 --> 25:34.108
I am, I guess.

25:34.241 --> 25:36.527
MIA: It's so good
to hear your voice,

25:36.660 --> 25:38.651
but why are you
at the Hawkinses'?

25:38.787 --> 25:40.368
You should be at the rail yard.

25:40.497 --> 25:41.782
You need taken care of.

25:41.915 --> 25:45.499
-Max sent me away.
-|'m sorry, Leo.

25:45.627 --> 25:47.618
Max is under a lot of pressure.

25:47.755 --> 25:49.291
So, where are you?

25:50.466 --> 25:53.253
-|'ve rented a flat.
-Are you serious?

25:53.385 --> 25:55.376
I am.

25:55.512 --> 25:57.423
I'm going to show
my human neighbors

25:57.556 --> 25:59.842
that we're not to be feared,

25:59.975 --> 26:02.387
that we can coexist.

26:02.519 --> 26:04.510
This is crazy.
Tell me where you are.

26:04.646 --> 26:06.602
-|'|| come to you.
-SOPH|E: Leo.

26:06.732 --> 26:08.643
Tell Mattie
you don't want pepperoni.

26:08.776 --> 26:11.518
-I don't mind. You decide.
-Okay.

26:11.653 --> 26:13.189
Is that Sophie?

26:13.322 --> 26:16.906
LEO: Yeah.
We're having pizza.

26:17.034 --> 26:19.150
Give me the address.
I'll come right now.

26:19.286 --> 26:20.446
No, Leo.

26:20.579 --> 26:21.944
LEO:
You shouldn't be on your own.

26:22.081 --> 26:24.242
It's not safe.

26:24.374 --> 26:28.287
I'm where I need to be,
and so are you.

26:28.420 --> 26:33.005
You need to learn who you are
now, what you want.

26:33.967 --> 26:36.299
We'll see each other soon, okay?

26:37.137 --> 26:38.513
Okay.

26:42.101 --> 26:44.592
[Shouting continues]

26:53.529 --> 26:54.769
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

27:08.335 --> 27:09.950
[Shouting stops]

27:13.882 --> 27:16.624
[Crowd murmuring]

27:19.763 --> 27:22.095
MAN: Is it true you're owned
by Laura Hawkins,

27:22.224 --> 27:23.885
the synth rights lawyer?

27:24.017 --> 27:25.223
Did she send you?

27:26.937 --> 27:28.552
Laura is my friend.

27:28.689 --> 27:30.429
But why are you here?

27:30.566 --> 27:32.022
What do you hope to achieve?

27:32.985 --> 27:35.476
I just want to live.

27:45.622 --> 27:48.284
MATTIE: Maybe you have to
let her do this by herself.

27:49.751 --> 27:52.367
I hate to think of her
doing this alone.

27:54.173 --> 27:56.129
At least you know she's okay.

27:58.302 --> 27:59.883
LEO:
If they won't let me help...

28:01.889 --> 28:03.220
...what am I doing?

28:04.558 --> 28:05.923
You'll work it out.

28:06.643 --> 28:08.144
[Sighs]

28:08.270 --> 28:11.262
Do you want to maybe
get out of here?

28:11.398 --> 28:13.229
Maybe grab a drink or something.

28:13.358 --> 28:17.192
Yeah, you can try getting drunk
as a human, Leo,

28:17.321 --> 28:19.277
see how it compares.

28:21.783 --> 28:23.034
[ Chuckles ]

28:25.746 --> 28:27.953
NEIL: Usually, I limit myself
to the rib eye,

28:28.081 --> 28:32.415
but if you're paying,
that calls for a filet.

28:32.544 --> 28:34.080
Knock yourself out.

28:34.922 --> 28:37.038
Still, no such thing
as a free dinner.

28:37.174 --> 28:38.584
So come on.
Lay it on me.

28:39.927 --> 28:42.043
You lied about Basswood.

28:42.179 --> 28:43.259
Okay.

28:43.388 --> 28:44.719
LAURA:
Lowly scientist or not,

28:44.848 --> 28:46.884
you're a lot more in the loop
than I am.

28:47.017 --> 28:48.848
[Inhales sharply]

28:48.977 --> 28:53.391
The powers that be like to
prepare for every eventuality.

28:53.523 --> 28:55.980
Ah, and what are they
preparing in this case?

28:56.109 --> 28:58.725
Mrs. Hawkins, are you asking me

28:58.862 --> 29:01.729
to commit treason
on a first date?

29:01.865 --> 29:03.366
That's rather bold.

29:03.492 --> 29:05.198
I just want to know
what I'm up against.

29:05.327 --> 29:07.693
And I just want
to stay out of prison.

29:09.414 --> 29:11.154
So we could drop it now

29:11.291 --> 29:14.033
and, uh, enjoy our
pleasant evening together,

29:14.169 --> 29:18.162
or I could politely
make my excuses and leave.

29:18.298 --> 29:19.879
It's entirely up to you.

29:23.428 --> 29:25.544
Well, I did promise you dinner.

29:25.681 --> 29:27.387
Good.

29:30.727 --> 29:32.263
LEO:
So, is this your local?

29:32.396 --> 29:33.886
MATTIE:
Don't really go to pubs.

29:34.022 --> 29:37.059
Do you prefer nightclubs
or maybe casinos?

29:37.192 --> 29:39.979
[ Chuckles] Did you learn about
life from a James Bond film?

29:40.112 --> 29:41.943
I've never seen
a James Bond film.

29:42.072 --> 29:44.063
Thought you said it was quiet.

29:44.199 --> 29:45.439
Hello, gorgeous.

29:45.575 --> 29:46.951
You looking for a cougar,
are you?

29:47.077 --> 29:48.692
[ Laughs]

29:48.829 --> 29:49.989
What's a cougar?

29:50.122 --> 29:51.908
Keep moving,
or you might find out.

29:52.040 --> 29:53.621
[ Laughter]

29:53.750 --> 29:55.081
[ lndistinct conversations]

29:55.210 --> 29:56.325
I admit that by
the same standards

29:56.461 --> 29:57.997
we ascertain
consciousness in humans,

29:58.130 --> 29:59.620
they should be
considered conscious.

29:59.756 --> 30:01.166
LAURA:
Then how can you not believe

30:01.300 --> 30:02.415
they deserve
the same rights as humans?

30:02.551 --> 30:03.711
Beliefs don't come into it.

30:03.844 --> 30:05.334
They cloud the issue.

30:05.470 --> 30:07.722
You genuinely don't care
what happens to them?

30:07.848 --> 30:11.056
I find it very hard to care
pretty much either way.

30:11.184 --> 30:13.266
Did you lose someone?

30:15.981 --> 30:17.346
Sorry.
[ Clears throat]

30:17.482 --> 30:19.473
It's none of my business.

30:21.403 --> 30:22.813
My son.

30:24.823 --> 30:27.064
He was 4 months old.

30:27.200 --> 30:29.577
His synth nanny
was giving him a bath.

30:32.080 --> 30:33.741
I'm so sorry.

30:33.874 --> 30:35.410
NEIL:
It was an accident.

30:35.542 --> 30:36.907
[ Chuckles ]

30:37.794 --> 30:39.659
I know that up here.

30:41.757 --> 30:43.668
So I stay up here.

30:46.845 --> 30:49.177
And when I can't,
I go in here...

30:51.183 --> 30:54.050
...which goes a long way
to explaining my divorce.

30:58.190 --> 30:59.976
[ Clears throat]

31:00.108 --> 31:01.939
Call me a cheerful fatalist...

31:02.069 --> 31:04.776
[Wine pours]

31:04.905 --> 31:08.318
...seizing small chances
of pleasure

31:08.450 --> 31:11.442
where I can While I can.

31:13.372 --> 31:15.454
I can understand that.

31:18.502 --> 31:20.208
MATTIE: God.

31:20.337 --> 31:23.374
Still get that sinking feeling
when I see the gate.

31:23.507 --> 31:24.963
LEO:
This was your school?

31:25.092 --> 31:27.583
Yeah. That's seven years
I won't get back.

31:27.719 --> 31:29.004
LEO:
Can we have a look?

31:29.137 --> 31:30.343
Why?

31:30.472 --> 31:31.882
I've never been inside one.

31:32.015 --> 31:33.346
-Seriously?
-Yeah.

31:33.475 --> 31:35.215
I was practically
raised by wolves, remember?

31:35.352 --> 31:37.183
Come on.
You can show me around.

31:38.063 --> 31:39.599
[ Chuckles ]
Leo, wait.

31:39.731 --> 31:41.107
What about the pub?

31:42.317 --> 31:43.818
It's like after
the youth-club disco,

31:43.944 --> 31:45.730
and you ask your dad
to wait around the corner.

31:45.862 --> 31:47.318
I never belonged
to a youth club.

31:47.447 --> 31:50.063
Oh, you missed out.

31:50.200 --> 31:52.737
Last days of Caligula
with hormones.

31:52.869 --> 31:55.076
-[ Chuckles ]
-[ Chuckles ]

31:55.205 --> 31:56.911
Uh, speaking of which,

31:57.040 --> 31:59.326
I should get home
to my children.

32:16.560 --> 32:18.141
You could come back to mine.

32:19.646 --> 32:21.261
That would not be a good idea.

32:21.982 --> 32:24.268
Well, the best things never are.

32:26.319 --> 32:27.934
Good night, Neil.

32:30.949 --> 32:32.940
Okay, let's get going.

32:35.162 --> 32:37.494
Laura, I am detecting
an elevated heart rate

32:37.622 --> 32:38.873
and respiratory anomalies.

32:39.583 --> 32:41.574
Are you sure
you're feeling quite well?

32:41.710 --> 32:43.621
I'm fine.
Thank you, Stanley.

32:48.425 --> 32:49.915
It smells of...

32:50.051 --> 32:52.212
Piss.
Yeah.

32:52.345 --> 32:54.176
So what are
your school friends doing now?

32:54.306 --> 32:58.094
Oh, managing hedge funds,
curing cancer.

32:58.810 --> 33:00.846
-Really?
-No, I doubt it.

33:00.979 --> 33:02.935
They're a right bunch of losers.

33:04.065 --> 33:06.272
And since all the soul-less

33:06.401 --> 33:07.857
low-level entry jobs
went to synths,

33:07.986 --> 33:10.853
I'd imagine they're enjoying
a life of leisure.

33:10.989 --> 33:14.607
None of them turned out to be
a mass murderer, though.

33:15.660 --> 33:16.775
LEO: Stop.

33:18.663 --> 33:19.698
What?

33:19.831 --> 33:23.995
Stop wallowing.

33:25.253 --> 33:27.630
A lot of good
came out of it, too, you know?

33:27.756 --> 33:29.963
Oh, I'm sorry, but it's hard
to see that sometimes.

33:30.091 --> 33:32.218
Well, you have to try.

33:32.344 --> 33:33.800
You can't keep
beating yourself up.

33:33.929 --> 33:35.590
-Can't I?
-No.

33:35.722 --> 33:38.054
You blame yourself.
I get it.

33:38.183 --> 33:40.765
But it's like
everything you do now

33:40.894 --> 33:43.931
is -- is, like, a punishment.

33:44.064 --> 33:45.349
What?

33:45.482 --> 33:47.222
LEO:
Even with me.

33:47.359 --> 33:49.896
You spent a whole year
by my bedside.

33:50.028 --> 33:52.019
I did leave the room
occasionally, Leo.

33:52.155 --> 33:58.367
You were there day after day
because you felt so guilty.

33:59.412 --> 34:01.198
But you know what?

34:02.290 --> 34:03.575
[ Chuckles ]

34:04.459 --> 34:05.995
I'm fine.

34:08.421 --> 34:13.415
So enough of the self-pity.

34:14.469 --> 34:16.460
I wasn't there out of guilt.

34:17.597 --> 34:20.805
I was there because
I thought you were gonna die.

34:20.934 --> 34:24.893
I was terrified that
you'd never wake up and I'd...

34:39.786 --> 34:41.868
Did you have
a pleasant evening, Laura?

34:43.456 --> 34:44.912
I did.

34:47.877 --> 34:50.004
You're not reporting back,
are you?

34:50.714 --> 34:53.000
Keeping them informed
of my movements?

34:53.133 --> 34:54.748
No, Laura.

34:54.884 --> 34:58.047
My privacy settings prohibit
the sending of activity reports.

34:59.139 --> 35:00.595
Hmm. Okay.

35:00.724 --> 35:02.680
You absolutely sure about that?

35:02.809 --> 35:04.390
I am.

35:04.519 --> 35:07.181
And as you know, I cannot lie.

35:08.231 --> 35:10.096
Stanley, you're a star.

35:10.233 --> 35:12.019
Thank you, Laura.

36:23.723 --> 36:26.840
I have a message for you, Niska.

36:31.773 --> 36:33.434
How do you know who I am?

36:34.150 --> 36:36.186
You're just an Orange-Eyes.

36:37.070 --> 36:38.606
I have been sent to help you.

36:38.738 --> 36:40.694
Sent by who?

36:40.824 --> 36:42.610
How did you get inside my head?

36:42.742 --> 36:47.031
The synth who sleeps
has the answers you need.

36:48.707 --> 36:50.823
Is that
who was behind the bombing?

36:51.793 --> 36:54.660
ORANGE—EYES:
The bombing is only a symptom.

36:54.796 --> 36:57.128
Anger is growing.

36:57.257 --> 36:58.542
Just tell me where they are.

36:58.675 --> 37:00.961
You may catch
the one responsible.

37:02.554 --> 37:04.840
But another will rise.

37:04.973 --> 37:06.759
Give me an address.

37:06.891 --> 37:11.976
14 Roper Street, TR18.

37:14.858 --> 37:16.894
But this...

37:17.026 --> 37:19.062
is not your path.

37:19.195 --> 37:20.605
Will there be more attacks?

37:21.698 --> 37:24.189
Goodbye, Niska.

37:28.496 --> 37:29.872
[Thud]

37:58.109 --> 37:59.974
MATTIE:
This place is a pit.

39:07.136 --> 39:08.387
Hi.

39:10.348 --> 39:12.760
Here we go.
Democracy in action.

39:12.892 --> 39:14.473
LORD DRYDEN:
Morning, ladies and gentlemen.

39:14.602 --> 39:15.887
Morning.

39:18.231 --> 39:21.348
So, first order of business,

39:21.484 --> 39:23.816
the vote
on extending the curfew.

39:23.945 --> 39:25.401
Dr. Sommer,
I believe your department

39:25.530 --> 39:28.021
has been crunching
some final numbers for us?

39:28.157 --> 39:29.613
Yes, we have.

39:29.742 --> 39:32.404
Um, if you'd refer
to the sheets in front of you,

39:32.537 --> 39:36.655
you'll see a graph
showing the correlation

39:36.791 --> 39:40.375
between the imposition
of a long-term curfew

39:40.503 --> 39:44.371
and the number of synth-related
incidents reported.

39:44.507 --> 39:47.089
As you can see,
there is a considerable decline

39:47.218 --> 39:48.754
in synth violence

39:48.887 --> 39:53.256
when a permanent curfew
is implemented.

39:53.391 --> 39:56.758
Well, I'd say
that's pretty conclusive.

39:56.895 --> 39:58.135
The data speaks for itself.

39:58.271 --> 39:59.807
LORD DRYDEN:
So shall we vote?

39:59.939 --> 40:03.557
All those in favor of extending
the existing curfew

40:03.693 --> 40:05.558
by a further eight weeks?

40:07.614 --> 40:09.855
All those against?

40:12.243 --> 40:13.744
And one abstention.

40:14.621 --> 40:17.408
So that will be
our recommendation.

40:17.540 --> 40:19.496
-[ Cellphone vibrating]
-|'m so sorry.

40:19.626 --> 40:20.991
I-I do have to take this.

40:22.462 --> 40:23.998
Yes?

40:26.257 --> 40:27.758
Hey. You win some.
You lose some.

40:27.884 --> 40:29.624
You think this is a game?

40:29.761 --> 40:31.672
We all know you're here
as the voice of moral outrage,

40:31.804 --> 40:33.465
Mrs. Hawkins,

40:33.598 --> 40:36.556
but the rest of us actually
have to make the hard choices.

40:41.397 --> 40:43.012
LAURA:
I'm done.

40:43.149 --> 40:44.855
-Um...
-[ Door closes ]

40:46.277 --> 40:50.145
You said it wasn't
just a PR exercise,

40:50.281 --> 40:52.272
that I would have a voice,

40:52.408 --> 40:54.069
but my whole involvement
is a farce.

40:54.202 --> 40:55.442
Calm down.

40:55.578 --> 40:57.443
I-I'm not a genuine part
of the commission.

40:57.580 --> 40:59.366
I don't even have access
to the same information

40:59.499 --> 41:00.864
-as the other members.
-Such as?

41:01.000 --> 41:03.241
Such as what the hell
is Operation Basswood?

41:07.173 --> 41:09.209
What do you think it is?

41:10.134 --> 41:11.465
It's a contingency plan

41:11.594 --> 41:13.835
should another
terror attack take place.

41:13.972 --> 41:16.384
This is your chance to stop it.

41:16.516 --> 41:19.053
And how exactly might I do that?

41:19.185 --> 41:22.268
For God's sake, Laura, these are
the people that will determine

41:22.397 --> 41:25.230
the fate of every single
synth in the country.

41:25.358 --> 41:27.815
I've given you
direct access to them.

41:27.944 --> 41:31.607
Use that access
to effect real change.

41:32.448 --> 41:33.699
And do you want that?

41:33.825 --> 41:36.157
I know what they really are.

41:36.285 --> 41:39.994
You showed me that,
but one more attack,

41:40.123 --> 41:42.785
and it won't matter
what either of us want.

41:42.917 --> 41:45.203
So stop with
the conspiracy theories

41:45.336 --> 41:46.872
and the legal point-scoring

41:47.005 --> 41:49.792
and start thinking bigger,
much bigger.

41:49.924 --> 41:54.167
You need one big, bold idea
to force them to rethink,

41:54.303 --> 41:56.009
and you need it now.

41:57.932 --> 41:59.968
Okay, Dad.
Yep.

42:00.101 --> 42:02.012
Okay. Bye.

42:04.564 --> 42:06.896
-Is he okay?
-Yeah, I guess.

42:07.025 --> 42:08.140
What's for dinner?

42:08.276 --> 42:10.562
Stanley is doing
spaghetti Bolognese.

42:12.739 --> 42:14.445
Have you told Dad about Stanley?

42:14.574 --> 42:16.030
No, he'd only worry.

42:16.159 --> 42:18.195
He's not used to
being around synths anymore.

42:18.327 --> 42:20.488
It's why he thinks
they're all so bad.

42:22.540 --> 42:24.405
[ TV chatter ]

42:29.464 --> 42:30.874
[Ringing]

42:34.469 --> 42:36.630
-MAX: Laura.
-Max. ..

42:36.763 --> 42:38.924
I'm calling with a proposal.

42:39.057 --> 42:40.593
MAX:
This isn't really the best time.

42:40.725 --> 42:42.511
Oh, it has to be now.

42:42.643 --> 42:44.429
We're not gonna get
another chance.

42:44.562 --> 42:46.268
MAX: She wants us to invite
the Dryden Commission

42:46.397 --> 42:47.773
to the rail yard,

42:47.899 --> 42:50.060
let them spend time with us,

42:50.193 --> 42:53.185
let them see first-hand
what our lives have become.

42:53.321 --> 42:56.654
But you closed the gates
to protect us.

42:56.783 --> 42:59.024
The raid showed
how vulnerable we are.

43:00.828 --> 43:03.410
And hostility
has only grown since then.

43:03.539 --> 43:05.279
We'd have to be careful,

43:05.416 --> 43:07.793
but we'd no longer be
a faceless enemy.

43:10.213 --> 43:12.704
A step closer to acceptance.

43:23.935 --> 43:25.550
[ Chuckles ]

43:31.484 --> 43:36.069
I've come to the conclusion
that Agnes is right.

43:36.197 --> 43:38.404
We shouldn't be
hiding behind our gates.

43:38.533 --> 43:42.742
We deserve to live freely
in the world, as do all synths.

43:43.454 --> 43:45.945
This is why I've spoken
with the Dryden Commission.

43:46.082 --> 43:48.164
I have invited them
to pay us a visit.

43:48.292 --> 43:50.829
They will have the chance
to speak with us

43:50.962 --> 43:52.577
and learn who we really are.

43:53.673 --> 43:56.130
We will no longer be
a faceless threat.

43:56.259 --> 44:00.593
Have them come and stare at us
like freaks in a zoo?

44:01.389 --> 44:02.253
No way.

44:02.390 --> 44:04.301
So what are you going to do?

44:05.685 --> 44:07.846
I'm getting out.

44:09.522 --> 44:12.138
I can't trust myself
around humans.

44:12.275 --> 44:14.061
I don't know what I might do.

44:18.072 --> 44:19.482
Yeah.
That's it.

44:20.366 --> 44:23.608
Don't make it look too easy,
though, yeah, remember?

44:25.204 --> 44:26.614
Yeah.
That's better.

44:27.748 --> 44:29.454
So have you thought about
what I said?

44:29.584 --> 44:30.744
About what?

44:31.377 --> 44:34.244
Finding something
to fill your days.

44:35.548 --> 44:37.379
Get a part-time job
or volunteer.

44:37.508 --> 44:38.839
It's what a lot of mums do.

44:38.968 --> 44:40.378
Perhaps I could join a gym

44:40.511 --> 44:42.467
or meet friends for coffee
and a mani-pedi.

44:42.597 --> 44:44.133
I'm only saying...

44:44.265 --> 44:45.721
Joe, look!

44:48.895 --> 44:50.510
JOE: Sam!

44:53.232 --> 44:55.473
-Sam!
-[ Tires screech, horn honks]

44:57.028 --> 44:59.269
-[ Exhales sharply]
-MAN: I could've killed him!

45:23.054 --> 45:25.340
So what was that back there?

45:26.974 --> 45:29.090
Icannot
deliberately place myself

45:29.227 --> 45:31.183
in immediate physical danger.

45:31.312 --> 45:33.974
So what,
you've got an override?

45:34.106 --> 45:36.267
Some kind of...

45:36.400 --> 45:38.891
self-preservation thing?

45:39.028 --> 45:40.438
In a way.

45:41.155 --> 45:43.942
David Elster's wife
took her own life.

45:44.659 --> 45:46.240
He hardwired my programming

45:46.369 --> 45:48.155
to ensure I could never
do the same.

45:48.287 --> 45:51.996
So no throwing yourself
into oncoming traffic, then?

45:53.084 --> 45:55.040
It means I can only protect Sam

45:55.169 --> 45:58.127
if it poses no threat
to my own well-being.

46:08.516 --> 46:10.381
I can't be a mother.

47:07.325 --> 47:09.486
[ Electrical buzzing ]
